==English==

===Verb===
{{en-verb|delous|ing}}

#To remove [[louse|lice]].  
#:''A [[veterinarian]] could delouse your [[dog]].''
#To apply [[insecticide|insecticides]] or insect repellants in order to be sure that no lice or other parasites are present.
#:''During the Korean Conflict, [[United States|US]] soldiers were deloused with [[DDT]] upon entering [[basic training]].''
#([[idiomatic]]:Computer [[Jargon]]) to remove [[malicious]] software such as viruses, trojans, spyware, or worms.
#:''A deloused computer may no longer be considered trustworthy.''

[[zh:delouse]]